      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 101,
      "message": "Per JPA documentation, the emf is responsible for caching DB connections, thus you have to close the emf when done, otherwise the connections may remain open; closing the em does not necessarily close the DB connection or release resources.\n\nFor tests, this doesn't really matter, but it's a source of connection and memory leaks in production code.",
